1
00:00:03,589 --> 00:00:08,360
Due to the approaching typhoon,
classes are canceled for the afternoon.

2
00:00:08,689 --> 00:00:11,143
Students who commute by bus or train

3
00:00:11,144 --> 00:00:12,559
please head home as soon as possible.

4
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:13,560
Can't get through?

5
00:00:13,590 --> 00:00:16,909
Yeah, the trains have stopped.
I was going to ask my family for a ride.

6
00:00:17,870 --> 00:00:20,089
If you don't mind...

7
00:00:21,329 --> 00:00:22,529
Want to come to my place?

8
00:00:23,379 --> 00:00:24,379
Huh?

9
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:25,200
"School Trip: Joined a Group I'm Not Close to" - After Story

10
00:01:25,540 --> 00:01:27,443
Severe Typhoon No. 2

11
00:01:27,444 --> 00:01:31,489
is moving north off the southeastern
coast of the Kanto region.

12
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:35,290
It is rapidly approaching
the Kanto region today,

13
00:01:35,540 --> 00:01:38,769
and the wind and rain are expected
to intensify through tomorrow.

14
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:41,149
According to railway companies,

15
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:44,038
due to the heavy rainfall,
not only the Shinkansen

16
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:48,283
but also local train services may
experience delays or suspensions.

17
00:01:48,284 --> 00:01:50,279
We urge the public to stay informed.

18
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:57,000
(Part 2: Typhoon Night)

19
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,480
Sorry for intruding.

20
00:02:07,029 --> 00:02:08,429
Yeah, you can leave your bag there.

21
00:02:09,208 --> 00:02:10,208
Where?

22
00:02:10,399 --> 00:02:11,399
Right here.

23
00:02:11,639 --> 00:02:12,639
Okay.

24
00:02:16,729 --> 00:02:18,580
Anyway, just make yourself at home.

25
00:02:20,270 --> 00:02:21,729
Oh, can I sit here?

26
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:22,860
Yeah.

27
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:31,860
Thank you...

28
00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:33,679
for inviting me.

29
00:02:34,059 --> 00:02:35,270
Yeah, of course.

30
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:37,580
Um...

31
00:02:38,119 --> 00:02:39,319
Is this really okay?

32
00:02:40,610 --> 00:02:41,610
Yeah.

33
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:43,130
What is?

34
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:45,660
Huh?

35
00:02:45,850 --> 00:02:46,850
No, that's not it.

36
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:48,990
Yeah?

37
00:02:50,059 --> 00:02:51,059
Uh, right.

38
00:02:51,380 --> 00:02:52,380
So, um...

39
00:02:53,479 --> 00:02:54,519
There's one more person...

40
00:02:54,679 --> 00:02:56,799
A friend of mine was
hoping to ride this out with us.

41
00:02:59,830 --> 00:03:01,529
Whoa, um...

42
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:04,820
Okay.

43
00:03:05,539 --> 00:03:06,539
Yeah.

44
00:03:08,279 --> 00:03:09,279
I get it.

45
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:11,770
Well...

46
00:03:11,929 --> 00:03:13,029
I'll ask.

47
00:03:14,639 --> 00:03:15,639
Okay.

48
00:03:15,809 --> 00:03:16,809
Okay.

49
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,500
Is everything okay?

50
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,095
If it's not a good time for
your family, Hioki-kun...

51
00:03:29,119 --> 00:03:30,270
it's really okay.

52
00:03:30,279 --> 00:03:31,479
It's not that.

53
00:03:34,089 --> 00:03:35,449
My mom...

54
00:03:36,529 --> 00:03:37,529
She, uh...

55
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:41,350
If you're okay with it...

56
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,520
she asked if you want to stay the night.

57
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:51,970
Huh?

58
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:54,715
When I invited you,

59
00:03:54,716 --> 00:03:57,000
a sleepover wasn't
exactly what I had in mind.

60
00:03:59,009 --> 00:04:00,009
You don't want to?

61
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:02,580
No...

62
00:04:02,940 --> 00:04:03,970
It's not that.

63
00:04:06,559 --> 00:04:07,849
I'm happy about it.

64
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,729
Because I get to be with you.

65
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,150
A sleepover with Watarai-kun?

66
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,220
That's fine, isn't it?

67
00:04:41,119 --> 00:04:42,119
What was that about?

68
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,679
See? That's my boy.

69
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:48,369
Is he very loud when he's in class?

70
00:04:49,279 --> 00:04:50,980
Not at all. He's very quiet.

71
00:04:51,309 --> 00:04:54,820
- But when Tsujitani is around...
- I knew it.

72
00:04:59,239 --> 00:05:00,239
Okay.

73
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,480
It's ready.

74
00:05:02,109 --> 00:05:03,109
Thanks.

75
00:05:06,459 --> 00:05:07,459
Oh, by the way.

76
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:09,250
What were you two talking about?

77
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,410
Huh?

78
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:12,610
With my mom.

79
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:14,620
You guys seemed to be having a good time.

80
00:05:14,899 --> 00:05:15,899
Oh...

81
00:05:16,970 --> 00:05:18,809
We were talking about school...

82
00:05:19,809 --> 00:05:20,809
and...

83
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:25,090
what you're like at home.

84
00:05:25,370 --> 00:05:27,370
Huh? She didn't say
anything weird, did she?

85
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,100
Not at all.

86
00:05:30,279 --> 00:05:32,100
She said you're really quiet at home.

87
00:05:32,359 --> 00:05:33,599
And that she gets a bit lonely.

88
00:05:35,019 --> 00:05:36,019
Oh...

89
00:05:37,049 --> 00:05:38,049
Also...

90
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,040
she thanked me.

91
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,040
Huh?

92
00:05:42,989 --> 00:05:45,219
For asking you to be in
my group for the school trip.

93
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:48,130
She said when you first
became a second-year...

94
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:51,270
she was worried you didn't
have any friends in your class.

95
00:05:53,209 --> 00:05:54,209
Is that so...

96
00:05:57,739 --> 00:05:59,010
And also...

97
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,230
Yeah?

98
00:06:02,739 --> 00:06:03,739
Oh.

99
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:06,069
She was curious if you have a girlfriend.

100
00:06:11,570 --> 00:06:12,870
What did you say?

101
00:06:13,279 --> 00:06:14,479
Nothing.

102
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:17,409
I really wanted to say,
"You're looking at him."

103
00:06:18,089 --> 00:06:19,569
But I changed the subject right away.

104
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:21,980
But...

105
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:23,580
one day, I'll properly...

106
00:06:24,170 --> 00:06:25,170
introduce myself to her.

107
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:28,990
As your boyfriend.

108
00:06:31,429 --> 00:06:32,429
Yeah.

109
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:37,440
Going to sleep?

110
00:06:38,489 --> 00:06:39,489
Are you sleepy?

111
00:06:40,410 --> 00:06:41,610
Yeah... a little.

112
00:06:42,429 --> 00:06:43,429
Yeah.

113
00:06:43,619 --> 00:06:44,619
All right.

114
00:06:46,470 --> 00:06:47,470
Okay.

115
00:06:53,869 --> 00:06:54,869
Mm-hmm.

116
00:06:55,190 --> 00:06:56,190
We're going to...

117
00:06:56,329 --> 00:06:57,329
sleep together, right?

118
00:06:58,109 --> 00:07:00,089
Huh? But the door doesn't lock.

119
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:02,080
We can just say I was half-asleep.

120
00:07:02,660 --> 00:07:03,860
We can play it off...

121
00:07:05,890 --> 00:07:07,330
Besides,

122
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,780
it's not like it's our first
time sleeping together.

123
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:18,559
Th-That's true.

124
00:07:27,429 --> 00:07:28,429
So...

125
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:44,320
that time,

126
00:07:45,109 --> 00:07:46,389
when I woke up in the morning...

127
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:49,350
I found you in my arms.

128
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:52,079
It surprised me,

129
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:53,920
but I was pretty happy.

130
00:07:54,649 --> 00:07:55,849
Huh? You noticed back then?

131
00:07:56,850 --> 00:07:57,850
Yeah.

132
00:07:58,380 --> 00:07:59,380
What?

133
00:07:59,929 --> 00:08:00,929
I just played it cool.

134
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,570
Yeah, I thought...

135
00:08:02,790 --> 00:08:04,120
you were doing it subconsciously.

136
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:05,510
Oh...

137
00:08:06,369 --> 00:08:07,999
That time, it was because...

138
00:08:09,309 --> 00:08:10,320
I couldn't sleep.

139
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,409
I thought if we were closer...

140
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,080
I'd feel more secure.

141
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:18,820
I see.

142
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:21,390
What about now?

143
00:08:23,279 --> 00:08:24,479
Now...

144
00:08:25,559 --> 00:08:27,319
I feel secure,

145
00:08:28,130 --> 00:08:29,390
and my heart is racing.

146
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,640
Me too.

147
00:08:49,929 --> 00:08:52,280
W-Wait a minute.
We definitely can't play this off.

148
00:08:52,479 --> 00:08:54,560
We'll cross that bridge when we get to it.

149
00:08:55,669 --> 00:08:56,719
There's no way.

150
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:28,130
Oh, sorry.

151
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:32,020
What is it?

152
00:09:36,270 --> 00:09:37,270
Who is it?

153
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:39,130
Ah, it's a message from the group chat.

154
00:09:39,359 --> 00:09:40,359
It's from Nakasato.

155
00:09:41,179 --> 00:09:42,179
What does it say?

156
00:09:42,266 --> 00:09:45,460
He's having a sleepover at Morisaki's with Hotta today.

157
00:09:45,499 --> 00:09:47,247
(Nakasato: Looks like I'm staying
over at Morisaki's with Hotta~)

158
00:09:47,272 --> 00:09:48,390
- Look.
- You're right.

159
00:09:50,239 --> 00:09:51,869
Wow, they're blowing up the chat.

160
00:09:56,869 --> 00:09:58,069
Yeah, brings back memories.

161
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:01,479
Oh, there are photos from back then, too.

162
00:10:04,049 --> 00:10:05,669
Oh, right.

163
00:10:06,599 --> 00:10:07,599
Hm?

164
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,900
There's something I've
been wondering. Can I ask?

165
00:10:10,969 --> 00:10:11,969
Yeah.

166
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:13,380
Go ahead.

167
00:10:14,669 --> 00:10:15,669
Um...

168
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:18,724
Before the school trip...

169
00:10:18,725 --> 00:10:19,950
did you already like me?

170
00:10:20,950 --> 00:10:21,950
Huh?

171
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,440
Uh...

172
00:10:25,590 --> 00:10:26,590
No...

173
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,800
I think I started to like you...

174
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,620
during the school trip.

175
00:10:31,179 --> 00:10:32,379
Huh, really?

176
00:10:32,710 --> 00:10:33,710
Yeah.

177
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,400
Then why did you ask
me to be in your group?

178
00:10:37,690 --> 00:10:38,690
That's because...

179
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:41,369
You probably don't remember,

180
00:10:42,619 --> 00:10:44,179
but right after we became second-years,

181
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:47,690
I overheard you talking about me.

182
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:50,650
Back then,

183
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:52,530
you said I...

184
00:10:53,419 --> 00:10:54,830
seemed kind.

185
00:10:57,679 --> 00:10:58,679
Did I say that?

186
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,080
You did.

187
00:11:01,179 --> 00:11:02,179
Well...

188
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:04,850
You probably just said it offhandedly,

189
00:11:06,419 --> 00:11:07,419
but...

190
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:10,670
usually, people only ever notice my looks.

191
00:11:12,219 --> 00:11:13,219
So...

192
00:11:14,380 --> 00:11:15,860
I was just really happy to hear that.

193
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:20,179
You see,

194
00:11:21,070 --> 00:11:23,419
I tend to believe the rumors about me.

195
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:26,170
I notice when people walk
on eggshells around me,

196
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:29,530
or make sarcastic, backhanded
comments, and it bothers me.

197
00:11:32,179 --> 00:11:33,179
But...

198
00:11:34,039 --> 00:11:35,165
when I'm with you,

199
00:11:35,166 --> 00:11:36,686
I don't worry about any of that stuff.

200
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:40,609
Isn't it the same with
Nakasato and the others?

201
00:11:41,090 --> 00:11:42,980
Those three are a different type.

202
00:11:43,190 --> 00:11:44,629
- Type?
- And also...

203
00:11:45,190 --> 00:11:46,410
they lack a certain purity.

204
00:11:48,469 --> 00:11:49,469
Pure...

205
00:11:49,859 --> 00:11:50,859
What do you mean?

206
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:52,570
Basically,

207
00:11:53,190 --> 00:11:55,190
the one who's the perfect
embodiment of my type...

208
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,500
is you.

209
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:02,020
Oh... is that so...

210
00:12:02,619 --> 00:12:03,619
Thank you.

211
00:12:10,969 --> 00:12:11,969
Oh...

212
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,840
Getting shy?

213
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,440
Oh, come on.

214
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:19,889
If you're my first love...

215
00:12:20,869 --> 00:12:21,969
then for the next one...

216
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:24,819
I don't think I'll have the
confidence to do it right.

217
00:12:25,859 --> 00:12:27,059
The next one?

218
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:30,366
- Oh, that's not what I meant.
- What 'next one'?

219
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,591
Are you already planning for a 'next one'?

220
00:12:31,592 --> 00:12:32,769
I just meant, what if... you know...

221
00:12:32,789 --> 00:12:34,630
- It was just a hypothetical.
- Nope.

222
00:12:35,549 --> 00:12:36,236
Absolutely not.

223
00:12:36,237 --> 00:12:38,023
- No way.
- Whoa, okay, okay.

224
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:39,144
You're too close, too close.

225
00:12:40,659 --> 00:12:41,659
So then.

226
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,040
Promise me you'll never
mention a 'next one' again.

227
00:12:44,669 --> 00:12:45,669
I promise.

228
00:12:45,830 --> 00:12:47,830
- Hey, what are you doing?
- Really?

229
00:12:48,479 --> 00:12:50,319
- Have you learned your lesson?
- That tickles!

230
00:12:50,369 --> 00:12:53,250
- Really? Say you're sorry.
- I've learned my lesson.

231
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,830
I'm sorry... I'm sorry...

232
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:57,109
I'm sorry.

233
00:12:59,330 --> 00:13:00,330
You're forgiven.

234
00:13:02,419 --> 00:13:03,919
Then can I ask you something?

235
00:13:04,609 --> 00:13:05,609
Hm?

236
00:13:06,263 --> 00:13:07,793
Why did you agree to go out with me?

237
00:13:09,852 --> 00:13:12,762
Is 'because I like you' not
a good enough answer?

238
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:14,750
It is, but...

239
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:17,270
Nope.

240
00:13:20,950 --> 00:13:22,340
I want more details.

241
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:23,950
What do you like about me?

242
00:13:27,719 --> 00:13:28,780
Well...

243
00:13:38,869 --> 00:13:41,349
- I'm going to bed.
- Hey, you're not getting away that easily.

244
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,946
- Tell me.
- Whoa, I know... Fine.

245
00:13:43,947 --> 00:13:45,220
Come on, tell me.

246
00:13:47,549 --> 00:13:49,040
The way you're so gentle.

247
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,199
The way you get jealous.

248
00:13:54,119 --> 00:13:55,740
And how you act all mature...

249
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:57,859
but you're actually really impatient.

250
00:14:00,409 --> 00:14:02,019
The way you're so cute.

251
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:06,590
Everything.

252
00:14:10,345 --> 00:14:12,426
All of it...

253
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:15,550
makes me love you so much.

254
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:17,910
From now on,

255
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,000
and for always...

256
00:14:21,979 --> 00:14:23,079
I'll love you the most.

257
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:26,770
Me too.

258
00:14:27,590 --> 00:14:29,070
I love you the most.

259
00:14:32,989 --> 00:14:34,829
Oh, getting shy again?

260
00:14:35,049 --> 00:14:38,049
I am not!

261
00:14:38,074 --> 00:14:39,013
(This story is a work of fiction)
